ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Pehle samjho â€” Hoisting hota kya hai?

JavaScript code 2 phase me execute hota hai:

Memory Creation Phase (Hoisting phase)
â†’ Sabhi variables aur functions ko memory me space milta hai.

Execution Phase
â†’ Code line by line execute hota hai.

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Function Declaration kya karti hai?

Example:

greet(); // âœ… ye kaam karega

function greet(){
  console.log("Hello");
}

ğŸ‘‰ Memory Creation Phase me kya hota hai?

JS engine line-by-line check karta hai.

Jab usse function declaration milta hai,
wo poora function code memory me store kar leta hai â€”
function ka naam + uska pura definition.

ğŸ’¡ So:

function greet(){ console.log("Hello"); }


â¡ Memory me ban gaya:
greet â†’ function(){ console.log("Hello"); }

Isliye code chalne se pehle hi JS ko pata hai â€œgreet kya haiâ€.
Toh hum use kahin se bhi call kar sakte hain â€” pehle bhi.

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Function Expression me kya hota hai?

Example:

sayHi(); // âŒ Error

const sayHi = function(){
  console.log("Hi");
}

ğŸ‘‰ Memory Creation Phase me kya hota hai?

JS dekhta hai: const sayHi = ...

Ab JS sirf variable ka naam memory me banata hai,
lekin value assign nahi karta (wo baad me Execution Phase me hota hai).

So:

Memory phase:
sayHi â†’ uninitialized (in TDZ)

Execution phase:
sayHi = function(){ console.log("Hi"); }


Toh jab line 1 pe sayHi() call hua â€” tab tak sayHi ke andar function assign hi nahi hua tha.
Isliye error aaya:

ReferenceError: Cannot access 'sayHi' before initialization

ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Simple Comparison Table
Type	Memory me kya store hota hai (Hoisting Phase)	Call pehle kar sakte ho?
Function Declaration	Function ka poora code	âœ… Yes
Function Expression	Sirf variable name (undefined / TDZ)	âŒ No
Arrow Function	Function Expression hi hota hai	âŒ No
